.TH DASALL-CLI 1 "2026-05-25" "DASALL" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dasall-cli \- installed DASALL structured control-plane client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dasall-cli
.I command
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dasall-cli
is the installed structured control-plane command for DASALL shipped by the
Debian and Ubuntu packages.

The bare command
.B dasall
is reserved for the terminal user interface. Use
.B dasall-cli
for automation, package scripts, maintainer guidance, and non-interactive
daemon control operations.

The v1 local control-plane operator path remains root/sudo-only. Use
.B sudo dasall-cli
for local daemon operations.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B help
Show command usage.
.TP
.B version
Print CLI version and schema support information.
.TP
.B config
Inspect, validate, plan, or apply local daemon configuration.
.TP
.B ping
Query daemon reachability.
.TP
.B readiness
Query daemon readiness summary.
.TP
.BI "run " JSON_PAYLOAD
Submit a unary request payload.
.TP
.BI "status " RECEIPT_REF " " OWNERSHIP_TOKEN " [" ACTOR_REF "]"
Query the status of an async receipt.
.TP
.BI "cancel " RECEIPT_REF " " OWNERSHIP_TOKEN " [" ACTOR_REF "]"
Cancel an async receipt.
.TP
.B diag
Query redacted diagnostics when the daemon configuration enables them.
.TP
.B knowledge
Refresh, retrieve, or inspect installed knowledge snapshots.
.SH PACKAGE-MODE DEPLOYMENT
For package-mode deployment, the canonical operator workflow name is:

.B sudo dasall-cli config

The canonical files remain:
.TP
.I /etc/default/dasall-daemon
Profile selection only.
.TP
.I /etc/dasall/daemon.json
Daemon override file. Only
.B daemon.*
keys are supported.

Validate a deployment configuration with:

.B . /etc/default/dasall-daemon && /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon --validate-only --profile-id="${DASALL_DAEMON_PROFILE_ID}" --config-file /etc/dasall/daemon.json
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/dasall-cli
Installed structured control-plane command.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/dasall
Installed TUI command.
.TP
.I /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon
Installed daemon binary.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/dasall-daemon/README.Debian
Package deployment notes.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dasall (1),
.BR dasall-daemon (8)